elements.title: René Vallon
elements.contents: ... that René Vallon (pictured) achieved the first aeroplane flight, and was the first aeroplane-related death, in China?

elements.title: The Americans
elements.contents: ... that the creator of The Americans drew inspiration for the show from his time as a CIA officer and a 2010 Russian spy scandal?

elements.title: Tjeerd van Andel
elements.contents: ... that Tjeerd van Andel was surprised to find heaps of giant clam shells around hot springs on his first dive to the Pacific ocean floor?

elements.title: Charles Herman Allen
elements.contents: ... that Charles Herman Allen, university administrator and American Civil War captain, opened the University of Wisconsin to female enrollment in 1863?

elements.title: organ of evacuated Polish railway workers in Moscow
elements.contents: ... that during World War I the organ of evacuated Polish railway workers in Moscow denounced the trade unions of the Warsaw–Vienna railway as "separatists"?
